interaction: Testosterone cypionate may increase the anticoagulant activities of Bivalirudin.
The risk or severity of adverse effects can be increased when Daunorubicin is combined with Flunisolide.
The risk or severity of hypertension can be increased when Alclofenac is combined with Etomidate.
The metabolism of Adenine can be decreased when combined with Estradiol acetate.
The metabolism of Olanzapine can be decreased when combined with Dexibuprofen.
The therapeutic efficacy of Bivalirudin can be decreased when used in combination with Medrogestone.
The risk or severity of bleeding and hemorrhage can be increased when Bivalirudin is combined with Dasatinib.
The risk or severity of serotonin syndrome can be increased when Duloxetine is combined with Safinamide.
